Welcome to the Learn JavaScript App. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our app.
1. Information We Collect
We collect minimal user data to ensure the functionality and performance of the app. This includes:
Usage Data:
Non-personal information such as app usage statistics, device type, operating system, and app version.
Optional Information:
If you voluntarily provide feedback or report bugs, we may collect your email address and feedback details.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information for:
Improving app functionality and user experience.
Identifying and fixing technical issues.
Sending optional updates or notifications, if you opt-in.
3. Data Storage and Security
We do not collect or store any personal data on our servers.
Non-personal usage data may be collected by third-party analytics services (e.g., Google Analytics for Firebase) to enhance app performance.
4. Third-Party Services
Our app may use trusted third-party services, such as:
Google AdMob
for advertisements.
These services may collect non-personal data as outlined in their privacy policies.
5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
The app does not use cookies.
However, third-party services may implement cookies or tracking technologies.
6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our app is suitable for users of all ages. However, we recommend parental guidance for younger users. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13 years of age.
7. Your Rights
As a user, you have the right to:
Access the data collected about your usage.
Request deletion of any optional data provided.
Opt-out of any non-essential data collection.
8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be reflected in this document, and you will be notified via an app update.
9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how your data is handled, please contact us at:
Email:
developer@codinghouse.in
Developer Name:
CODING HOUSE
By using the Learn JavaScript App, you agree to this Privacy Policy. Thank you for trusting us with your learning journey!
